Day 3 - Chapter 3
Nested if and elif statements
=> Nested if and elif statements let you handle more complex decisions: “if this and also that… otherwise if something else…”.

Example for if statement:- 
age = 20
has_license = True
if age >= 18:
    print("You are an adult.")
    if has_license:
        print("You can drive.")
    else:
        print("You are an adult but cannot drive.")
else:
    print("You are not an adult.")

Example for elif statement:- 
score = 72
if score >= 90:
    print("Grade A")
elif score >= 80:
    print("Grade B")
elif score >= 70:
    print("Grade C")
else:
    print("Grade D")

Example for Nested + elif statement:-
age = 25
income = 60000

if age >= 18:
    if income >= 100000:
        print("High-income adult.")
    elif income >= 50000:
        print("Mid-income adult.")
    else:
        print("Low-income adult.")
else:
    print("Minor.")


